inference: Final Answer: \\boxed{\$920.25}. I hope it is correct.
ground_truth: After two years, at a 4.5 percent annual interest rate, the investment will have grown to $10000 \cdot (1.045)^2 = 10920.25$, so the interest earned is $10920.25 - 10000 = \boxed{920.25}$.
